Clean dataset

Aim at cleaning, organising and only keep necessary info from fat raw data using the function âclean_raw_fat_dataâ

The function :

  • removes all âmass_Jxxâ columns,
  • removes columns: âsamples_marrow_fat_rateâ, âsamples_marrow_fat_rate_without_residualsâ, âbone_marrow_fat_rate_meanâ, âbone_marrow_fat_rate_mean_without_residualsâ,âestimated_bcâ,âestimated_bc_without_residualsâ, âcommentsâ and any columns after,
  • removes all replicated samples tested after J-9, etcâ¦ /ex âHip_B_046-J12â
  • removes empty raws after 233rd row
  • removes raws corresponding to Buffalo_01 â> a test sample that wasnât harvested following the study desidn (but opportunistically) and must, thus, be excluded because it wasnât

Save cleaned dataset

Aim at saving cleaned data for fat analyses âsave_cleaned_dataâ

The function takes 2 arguments :

  • cleaned_data : cleaned raw data for fat analyses (after using clean_raw_fat_data function)
  • filename : the name we want the dataset to be saved under

The cleaned dataset is saved under ./output/clean_fat_data/
